# Frontend Rules — apps/web
# Applies to: all files inside apps/web/
# Extends: root .windsurfrules

## NEXT.JS APP ROUTER PATTERNS

### Page files (page.tsx)
- Server Component by default — no 'use client' unless interactivity needed
- Fetch data using async/await directly in the component
- Export metadata from page files: `export const metadata: Metadata = { title: '...' }`
- Use `loading.tsx` for Suspense skeleton loaders
- Use `error.tsx` for route-level error boundaries
- Private route components live in `_components/` subfolder (prefixed underscore = private to route)

```tsx
// CORRECT page.tsx pattern
import type { Metadata } from 'next';
import { EmployeeTable } from './_components/EmployeeTable';
import { getEmployees } from '@/lib/api/employees';

export const metadata: Metadata = { title: 'Employees | HRMS' };

export default async function EmployeesPage() {
  const employees = await getEmployees();
  return <EmployeeTable employees={employees} />;
}
```

### Client Components ('use client')
- Add 'use client' ONLY when component uses: useState, useEffect, useRef, onClick, onChange, browser APIs, Socket.io, Supabase Realtime
- Keep client components small — they cannot use async/await for data fetching
- Prefer passing data as props from Server Components into Client Components

### Layout files (layout.tsx)
- layout.tsx wraps all child pages — use for persistent sidebar, header, providers
- Do NOT fetch per-page data in layout.tsx
- Providers (QueryClientProvider, ThemeProvider) go in root layout only

## COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE

### File structure for complex components
```
components/hrm/EmployeeCard/
├── EmployeeCard.tsx       ← main component
├── EmployeeCard.test.tsx  ← unit tests
└── index.ts               ← re-export only
```

### Simple components (< 80 lines) — flat files
```
components/ui/
├── Badge.tsx
├── Spinner.tsx
└── Avatar.tsx
```

### Component template
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import type { ComponentProps } from './types'; // if needed

interface MyComponentProps {
  // explicit prop types always
  className?: string;
}

export function MyComponent({ className }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('base-classes', className)}>
      ...
    </div>
  );
}
```

## TAILWIND RULES FOR THIS APP

### Color tokens (use ONLY these — never raw hex)
- bg-background / text-foreground       — page backgrounds
- bg-primary / text-primary-foreground  — primary actions, active states
- bg-muted / text-muted-foreground      — subtle backgrounds, helper text
- bg-destructive                        — delete, error states
- border-border                         — all borders
- text-success (green-600/green-400)    — approved, present states
- text-warning (yellow-600/yellow-400)  — pending, warning states

