## DATA FETCHING PATTERNS

### TanStack Query — queryKey conventions
```typescript
// Always use array queryKeys with this hierarchy:
['employees']                          // all employees
['employees', employeeId]              // single employee
['employees', employeeId, 'leaves']    // employee's leaves
['attendance', { month, year }]        // attendance with params
['leave-balance', employeeId]          // leave balance
['chat', 'channels']                   // all channels
['chat', 'messages', channelId]        // channel messages
```

### Mutation pattern
```typescript
const { mutate, isPending } = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (data: LeaveRequestInput) => api.post('/leaves', data),
  onSuccess: () => {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['leaves'] });
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['leave-balance', user.id] });
    toast.success('Leave request submitted');
  },
  onError: (error: AppError) => {
    toast.error(error.message ?? 'Something went wrong');
  },
});
```

## FORM PATTERNS

### Always use React Hook Form + Zod
```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { leaveRequestSchema, type LeaveRequestInput } from '@hrms/types';

const form = useForm<LeaveRequestInput>({
  resolver: zodResolver(leaveRequestSchema),
  defaultValues: { leaveTypeId: '', reason: '' },
});
```

### Form field pattern (shadcn FormField)
```tsx
<FormField
  control={form.control}
  name="leaveTypeId"
  render={({ field }) => (
    <FormItem>
      <FormLabel>Leave Type</FormLabel>
      <FormControl>
        <Select onValueChange={field.onChange} defaultValue={field.value}>
          ...
        </Select>
      </FormControl>
      <FormMessage /> {/* auto-shows Zod error */}
    </FormItem>
  )}
/>
```

## PWA / SERVICE WORKER
- Service Worker is at `public/sw.js` — do not put SW logic in app/ directory
- Permission request for push MUST be inside a button onClick handler
- Check `Notification.permission` before showing the enable-notifications prompt
- Store push subscription by POSTing to `/api/notifications/subscribe`

## PERFORMANCE CHECKLIST FOR EVERY NEW PAGE
- [ ] Is the page a Server Component? (default yes)
- [ ] Are heavy components lazy-loaded with `dynamic()`?
- [ ] Are images using `next/image`?
- [ ] Is data fetched on the server (Server Component) or via useQuery (Client Component)?
- [ ] Are queryKeys granular enough for targeted invalidation?
